How to Integrate Everyone’s Work in a Common GitHub Repo
1. Branching Strategy
Use a feature-branch workflow:
Each person creates a branch for their feature (e.g., feature/backend-episode-crud, feature/frontend-dashboard, feature/ai-integration).
Main branches:
main (production-ready)
develop (integration branch for all features)
2. Pull Requests & Code Reviews
Each member submits a pull request (PR) from their feature branch to develop.
Leads (Carol for backend, Eve for frontend) and Bob (architect) review PRs for quality and consistency.
QA (Heidi) tests features on the develop branch.
3. Regular Syncs
Daily standups to discuss progress and blockers.
Weekly integration meetings to merge and test features together.
4. Integration Steps
After successful code review and testing, merge PRs into develop.
Once all features are integrated and tested, merge develop into main for release.
5. CI/CD Automation
Ivan sets up pipelines to:
Run tests on every PR.
Deploy the latest develop branch to a staging environment.
Deploy main to production.
6. Documentation
Judy updates the README, API docs, and user guides as features are merged.
All members document their code and usage in their PRs.
